    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "No new keys today - this one is about flow. Same word, again and again, until your fingers stop thinking and just move. Flow, not force."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "Hands on the home row, thumbs over the space bar, eyes off the keys. Repeat each word at an even pace - same gap between every tap. Don't chase speed, just lock in the beat."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "🎶",
      "title": "Even beat",
      "text": "Pick a tempo you can hold and stay there. Steady beats fast every time - smooth and even wins, jerky and rushed loses. Let the rhythm carry you."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "ask ask ask ask ask",
      "finger": "pink",
      "title": "Rhythm: ask",
      "hint": "Repeat it like a loop: ask - ask - ask. Same gap every time, no rushing."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "sad sad sad sad",
      "finger": "orange",
      "title": "Rhythm: sad",
      "hint": "Keep the beat steady: sad - sad - sad. Flow, not force."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "lad lad lad lad",
      "finger": "orange",
      "title": "Rhythm: lad",
      "hint": "Hold the tempo to the end: lad - lad - lad. Don't speed up at the finish."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Feel it? Your fingers start to grab the whole word at once instead of one letter at a time. That is muscle memory locking in - the quiet payoff of typing the same thing on a steady beat."
    },
